            "body": "This is also why #25822 was incorrect, I'd assume.\r\n\r\nAs `on_bytes` of foldexpr was relying on `nvim_buf_attach`'s `on_bytes` to return the correct start row, old row and new row, but pressing `O` means the start row is the same as the new index, meaning the row range is one-off from the correct one. This can also be confirmed by instead doing `A<Enter>`, and the foldcolumn is correctly updated",
